    "created_at": "2018-05-31T21:24:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2018-05-31T21:24:28Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "As for fairness, I don't mind spending 0.000000005 ETH for the require statement. For 1 ETH, I could run that line of code 200 Million times. Also, sometimes scripts will be using the contract. Since the transaction would revert, our Dapps can be less complex.\r\n\r\nImagine having to paste a chunk of code to check balance into your Dapp every time you want to do a transfer or use a contract. \r\n\r\nIf the user is intentionally paying more than what he has, then it simply won't work. No need to waste his/our gas. Only miners would support punishing users by using all of their available gas on a transaction revert. \r\nFor the sake of the network, minimizing gas cost allows more transactions per block and therefore more transactions per second.",
